  },
  {
    title: "Reliability is Non-Negotiable",
    description: "For government systems handling citizen data, 99.9% uptime isn't aspirational—it's required. I design for failure: retry mechanisms, dead-letter queues, circuit breakers, and comprehensive monitoring aren't optional extras."
  },
  {
    title: "Data Ownership and Boundaries",
    description: "Services should own their data. I've learned through experience that cross-service database queries create tight coupling and deployment nightmares. Clear boundaries enable independent scaling and team autonomy."
  },
  {
